head_commit.message:
perf(agent): execute tool calls concurrently to improve performance

The tool execution logic was refactored to use `for_each_concurrent` and `Arc<Mutex<Vec<ToolCallOutput>>>` to allow concurrent execution of tool calls. This change improves performance by reducing the time spent waiting for sequential tool executions. Additionally, error handling and logging were enhanced to provide better visibility into tool execution failures.

head_commit.message:
feat(agent): add task evaluator tool and enhance agent loop logic

Introduce a new task evaluator tool to determine task completion status and provide context for iterative refinement. Enhance the agent loop logic to handle task evaluation, optimize loop efficiency, and minimize resource consumption. Also, add support for saving task state during each loop iteration and improve the handling of tool call responses.

head_commit.message:
feat(swarms-macro): add macro for defining tools with attributes

Introduce a new macro `swarms-macro` to simplify the creation of tools with attributes like name, description, and argument metadata. The macro generates the necessary structs and implementations for tool definitions, reducing boilerplate code and improving maintainability. This change also includes updates to `Cargo.toml` to integrate the new macro and an example demonstrating its usage.
